This paper is about visual tracking using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel deep network architecture, which involves training the network in an end-to-end manner, indicating that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of adaptive aggregation subnetworks, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with the integration of RGB and thermal infrared data, which could make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on tracking could also make it relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
